[2] Cholera, prisoners - Myanmar
Date: Fri, 30 Sep 2005
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Democratic Voice of Burma [edited]
<http://english.dvb.no/news.php?id=5659>

Due to the severe cholera outbreak in Tharawaddy Prison in central Burma,
more than 40 inmates including a political prisoner died on 27 Sep 2005
alone, according to sources close to the prison.
The dead political prisoner is said to be an Arakan Communist Party member,
a native of Yanbye in western Burma, who had been detained since 1986.
According to a prison staff member, who doesn't want to be named, prison
governor Myint Swe told a medic not to record the reason for [the
prisoner's] death as cholera.
Prisoners' families are very anxious for the welfare of their loved ones.
They urged Rangoon-based International Committee for Red Cross (ICRC)
representatives to visit and inspect the prison as soon as possible.
--
