[7] Cholera - Guinea-Bissau
Date: Wed, 28 Sep 2005
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: XinHuaNet.com [edited]
<http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2005-09/28/content_3556903.htm>

The death toll from Guinea-Bissau's cholera outbreak now stands at 280, and
the deadly waterborne disease has now spread to the eastern regions of
Bafata and Gabu, according to reports reaching here from Bissau on Wed, 28
Sep 2005. A Health Ministry official was quoted as saying on Tuesday that
16 544 cholera cases have been recorded and the worst-affected area has
been Bissau, with 60 deaths from over 9000 cases.
The WHO warned Tue, 27 Sep 2005 that this year's region-wide cholera
epidemic, afflicting 8 West African states, is the worst in years,
according to the official.
--
