[10] Cholera - Uganda
Date: Fri, 23 Sep 2005
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: ReliefWeb.int [edited]
<http://www.reliefweb.int/rw/RWB.NSF/db900SID/ACIO-6GHRB9?OpenDocument>

Uganda's Health Ministry has sounded a cholera alert, informing the general
public that the disease is still being reported in 8 districts of the
country, according to a report from Radio Uganda on Fri, 23 Sep 2005. The
Director General of health services from the ministry, Sam Okware, said in
a press release that 8 districts which reported cholera cases are Kampala,
Hoima, Masindi, Kasese, Bundibugyo, Kotido, Arua and Nebbi.
He said 8 new cases have been confirmed in Kampala this week. "Kampala City
Council has opened a new cholera treatment center at Komamboga Health
Center to manage all cholera patients in the city," said Okware.
